docs.abstract: A redaction error in an inspector general report brought to light another bulk-collection program ended in the aftermath of Edward Snowden’s leaks.
docs.snippet: A redaction error in an inspector general report brought to light another bulk-collection program ended in the aftermath of Edward Snowden’s leaks.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Drug Enforcement Administration secretly collected data in bulk about Americans’ purchases of money-counting machines — and took steps to hide the effort from defendants and courts — before quietly shuttering the program in 2013 amid the uproar over the disclosures by the National Security Agency contractor Edward Snowden, an inspector general report found.

headline.main: D.E.A. Secretly Collected Bulk Records of Money-Counter Purchases

docs.abstract: Mr. Gaetz came to Washington as the son of the Florida Senate president, with a reputation for deal making. His incendiary antics have put that rap behind him.
docs.snippet: Mr. Gaetz came to Washington as the son of the Florida Senate president, with a reputation for deal making. His incendiary antics have put that rap behind him.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Matt Gaetz of Florida came to Washington in 2017 with a reputation for bipartisan deal-cutting in the State Legislature — then spent a year idling behind the slow-moving minivans in the House Republican Conference like a Mustang stuck in traffic.

headline.main: Matt Gaetz Is a Congressman Liberals Love to Loathe. It’s All Part of the Plan.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After years of effort, scientists at the Fish and Wildlife Service had a moment of celebration as they wrapped up a comprehensive analysis of the threat that three widely used pesticides present to hundreds of endangered species, like the kit fox and the seaside sparrow.

headline.main: Interior Nominee Intervened to Block Report on Endangered Species
headline.print_headline: Interior Nominee Helped Quash Pesticide Report

docs.abstract: A Justice Department motion to invalidate the entire Affordable Care Act gave Democrats an opening to press their health care agenda and move beyond the Mueller report.
docs.snippet: A Justice Department motion to invalidate the entire Affordable Care Act gave Democrats an opening to press their health care agenda and move beyond the Mueller report.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration’s decision to ask a federal appeals court to invalidate the Affordable Care Act has given House Democrats a new opening to pursue what they see as a winning political strategy: moving past talk of impeachment to put kitchen-table issues like health care front and center.

headline.main: Democrats Pivot Hard to Health Care After Trump Moves to Strike Down Affordable Care Act
headline.print_headline: Move to Nullify  Health Care Act  Roils Democrats

docs.abstract: Angry counterprotesters far outnumbered the small band of far-right demonstrators who turned out in Washington, and then quickly dispersed, on the anniversary of the violent Charlottesville rally.
docs.snippet: Angry counterprotesters far outnumbered the small band of far-right demonstrators who turned out in Washington, and then quickly dispersed, on the anniversary of the violent Charlottesville rally.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After weeks of hype, white supremacists managed to muster just a couple of dozen supporters on Sunday in the nation’s capital for the first anniversary of their deadly rally in Charlottesville, Va., finding themselves greatly outnumbered by counterprotesters, police officers and representatives of the news media.

headline.main: Rally by White Nationalists Was Over Almost Before It Began
headline.print_headline: White Nationalist Rally Drowned Out by Crowd Of Anti-Hate Protesters

docs.abstract: The president’s eldest daughter stands alone in the White House in refusing to condemn the press. Her emotional comments about family separations were closer to White House policy.
docs.snippet: The president’s eldest daughter stands alone in the White House in refusing to condemn the press. Her emotional comments about family separations were closer to White House policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Ivanka Trump appeared on Thursday to break step with two of the most contentious issues surrounding her father’s administration: She disagreed with President Trump’s position that the press is the enemy of the people, and she said the administration’s hard-line stance on immigration that resulted in separating children from their parents was a “low point” during her time in the White House.

headline.main: Are Journalists the Enemy of the People? Ivanka Trump Says They’re Not
headline.print_headline: A Trump Who Refuses To Condemn Journalism
